  "elapsed_s": 10.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And of course, when Horthy did not want to-- did not agree and did not want to pick up the Jews and send them to their deaths, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] the country was overrun by the Germans.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Horthy Miklos.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He was the-- he was an admiral, and he was the ruler of Hungary.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And, and of course, he was replaced by a, a, a real anti-Semite.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS] And then, of course, the Germans were in.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And so they did-- they finished the rest of his job, and after they finished picking up all the Jews in all the towns around [NON-ENGLISH], then we were shipped, shipped out in the middle of the night from ghetto [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It took us four days to-- before we reached our destination.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We realized that the-- this degrading process that, that was being used on us was not just a temporary situation, that once we were moved from ghetto [NON-ENGLISH], it-- we became suspicious that this, this may be lethal.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "There were-- we were so crammed in, into cattle cars, that not all of us could, could sit at the same time.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Some of us had to doze off-- excuse me-- by standing up and by leaning on each other's shoulders.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "With us was a barrel of water-- not a big barrel, but something like five or 10 gallons, possibly, and a bed pan.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Yes, we had to do our basic human functions with just a single blanket as a screen.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Four days later, we arrived at our destination on a Friday evening, and all night long they kept the cattle cars locked.",
      "word_count": 26
    }
  ],
